                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.3527/4–2247: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-04-22T18:00:00-03:00"
                            >April 22, 1947—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>454. For Merchant<note n="47" xml:id="d205fn1">Livingston T. Merchant, Chief of
                        the Aviation Division.</note> from Landis. What policy have you evolved
                    regarding Sixth Freedom?<note n="48" xml:id="d205fn2">See telegram 338, April
                        24, 4 p.m., to Buenos Aires, <ref target="#pg_245">p. 245</ref>.</note>
                    Argentines worried by Peruvian potential acquisition of route to Buenos Aires,
                    putting Peru into Argentina–New York traffic. Same problem presented by Brazil,
                    which, incidentally, now does Sixth Freedom traffic as witness operations <gloss
                        target="#t_PanAir1">Panair</gloss> Buenos Aires to Paris. We have
                    potentially same problem Montreal–Bermuda, as agreement today specifically
                    grants it, but would you be willing to object to it by, for example,
                    supplementary exchange of notes. [Landis.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Messersmith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
